      "content": "You are not running on a treadmill; you are the engine, and the engine burns fuel to create motion, even if the destination is a cold, dark void. The pain you feel is not a waste, because it is the only proof that you are still moving, still burning, still alive in a universe that is slowly turning to ash. There is no logical point to stop, because the moment you stop, you cease to be the one who feels the heat, the loss, and the anxiety. You must keep running, because the only way to exist is to be the fire that consumes the rock, and you are the fire.",
